<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>	<item><state>CT</state><who>People with Bipolar /depression</who><category><shortname>support</shortname><id>33</id><name>support</name></category><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : x-small"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #000000"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Welcome to the DBSA, "DEPRESSION BIPOLAR SUPPORT ALLIANCE"&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="font-size : x-small"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #000000"&gt;serving Greater New Haven and Westport.&lt;/span&gt; Share in discussions and experience support in a safe and non judgmental setting with others who are dealing as well as coping with depression and bipolar disorder . There is much evidence that support groups can be beneficial and therapeutic for those of us with these illnesses. A support group atmosphere can empower us through sharing, listening, and learning about personal experiences and how each one of us strives to manage our illness.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : x-small"&gt;The Greater New Haven group meets in &lt;span style="color : #ff0000 ; text-decoration : underline"&gt;BRANFORD&lt;/span&gt; every &lt;span style="color : #ff0000 ; text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;Monday&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span style="color : #ff0000 ; text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : small"&gt;Tuesday&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; evening from 6-8 at BHCare (formerly Harbor Health Services).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : x-small"&gt;The &lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #ff0000"&gt;WESTPORT&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; group meets at the Hall-Brooke Facility every &lt;span style="color : #ff0000 ; text-decoration : underline"&gt;Thursday&lt;/span&gt; evening from 6-8 PM. There is no charge. You do not have to join Meetup to attend a meeting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : x-small"&gt;PLEASE NOTE : There are usually 8-12 regularly attending members at each meeting. The number of people attending each week is not reflected in the RSVP section on this page.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : x-small"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : x-small"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #000000"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are joining via Meetup.com please use your first name or&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="font-size : x-small"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration : underline"&gt;&lt;span style="color : #000000"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;initial ONLY&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color : #000000"&gt;If you use your full name there is the potential that a Google search will connect your name with this group.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : x-small"&gt;For more information call or write @&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size : x-small"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="mailto:branforddbsa@gmail.com" target="_blank"&gt;branforddbsa@gmail.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
